{"title": "The Future of AI: Trends to Watch in 2025", "article_text": "Artificial intelligence is evolving faster than ever. In 2025 we expect larger language models, more pervasive edge‑AI, tighter integration with IoT, and new ethical frameworks. Companies will focus on AI‑augmented productivity, while regulators will push for transparency and fairness. The rise of multimodal models will enable richer human‑computer interaction, and AI‑generated content will become a mainstream creative tool.

Key challenges include data privacy, model interpretability, and the environmental impact of training massive models. However, advancements in efficient architectures and green AI research promise to mitigate these concerns.

Overall, the AI landscape in 2025 will be characterized by greater accessibility, responsible deployment, and a shift from hype to real‑world value creation."}
